&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cardio-Respiratory Directorate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Home Oxygen Service and Pulmonary Rehabilitation Nurse/Physiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week, permanent post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Advert&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Home Oxygen Service and Pulmonary Rehabilitation Teams at University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust. We are both a dynamic and progressive departments actively engaged in national audit and research. The successful applicant will have an active role to play in the delivery of these services across UHL sites and Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland. We are looking for a dynamic, highly motivated, enthusiastic and experienced nurse or physiotherapist to work across Pulmonary Rehabilitation and Home Oxygen services. This person will be required to work flexibly across hospital and community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to take an active role in all phases of the UHL Pulmonary Rehabilitation and Home Oxygen service pathways. The applicant will have a very high standard of clinical and communication skills, be able to work independently as well as being an excellent team player and actively engage in departmental and service development as well as regular audit and participation in research. You will have experience of respiratory and/or pulmonary rehabilitation in addition to extensive clinical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah Williams/ Emma ChaplinJob titleHome Oxygen Nurse/ Senior Pulmonary Rehabilitation physiotherapistEmail addresssarah.l.williams@uhl-tr.nhs.ukTelephone number 0116 2502880 Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit, please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Williams or Emma Chaplin&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Home Oxygen Nurse and Senior Pulmonary Rehabilitation Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glenfield Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0116 2502880/ 2583181&lt;/p&gt;
